        content:
          '<p>Welcome to Yorkshire calls in investigators over its boss Gary Verity’s expenses</p><p>The Yorkshire tourism body that has appointed independent investigators to examine its chief executive’s lavish expenses accepted £14.89m in public money over the past five years, the Guardian has learned.</p><p>More than half of <a href="https://www.yorkshire.com/">Welcome to Yorkshire</a>’s (WTY) income derived from the taxpayer between 2013 and 2018 but the organisation will not answer detailed questions about how that money was spent by its boss, Sir Gary Verity, who resigned last Friday.</p> <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2019/mar/29/scandal-hit-yorkshire-tourism-group-paid-public-funds-gary-verity">Continue reading...</a>',
